{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Binding","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever the source property changes, the same value is applied to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"target property; for instance, the following binding:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_DEFAULT);"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"will cause the property named “property-b” of ","type":"text"},{"code":"object2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be updated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"every time [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.set","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or the specific accessor changes the value of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property “property-a” of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object1"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to create a bidirectional binding between two properties"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of two ","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, so that if either property changes, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"other is updated as well, for instance:"}]},{"code":["  g_object_bind_property (object1, \"property-a\",","                          object2, \"property-b\",","                          G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL);"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"will keep the two properties in sync.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also possible to set a custom transformation function (in both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directions, in case of a bidirectional binding) to apply a custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"transformation from the source value to the target value before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applying it; for instance, the following binding:"}]},{"code":["  g_object_bind_property_full (adjustment1, \"value\",","                               adjustment2, \"value\",","                               G_BINDING_BIDIRECTIONAL,","                               celsius_to_fahrenheit,","                               fahrenheit_to_celsius,","                               NULL, NULL);"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"will keep the “value” property of the two adjustments in sync; the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"celsius_to_fahrenheit"},{"type":"text","text":" function will be called whenever the “value”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment1"},{"type":"text","text":" changes and will transform the current value"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the property before applying it to the “value” property of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"adjustment2"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Vice versa, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"fahrenheit_to_celsius","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function will be called whenever"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the “value” property of "},{"code":"adjustment2","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" changes, and will transform the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current value of the property before applying it to the “value” property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of ","type":"text"},{"code":"adjustment1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" does not resolve cycles by itself; a cycle like","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["  object1:propertyA -> object2:propertyB","  object2:propertyB -> object3:propertyC","  object3:propertyC -> object1:propertyA"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"might lead to an infinite loop. The loop, in this particular case,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be avoided if the objects emit the "},{"code":"GObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"notify"},{"code":" signal only if the value has effectively been changed. A binding is implemented using the `GObject`notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" signal, so it is susceptible to all the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"various ways of blocking a signal emission, like [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.signal_stop_emission"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.signal_handler_block"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A binding will be severed, and the resources it allocates freed, whenever","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either one of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" instances it refers to are finalized, or when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance loses its last reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bindings for languages with garbage collection can use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.Binding.unbind"},{"type":"text","text":"] to explicitly release a binding between the source"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and target properties, instead of relying on the last reference on the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"binding, source, and target instances to drop."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding"},{"text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GBinding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Binding"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GBinding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifi